'''洛杉磯之戰'''（{{lang-en|Battle of Los Angeles}}），又稱'''洛杉磯大空襲'''（{{lang|en|The Great Los Angeles Air Raid}}），是指1942年發生在[[美國|美國]][[洛杉磯|洛杉磯]]的一次[[UFO|UFO]]事件。1942年2月24日午夜至1942年2月25日凌晨2點，洛杉磯[[聖塔莫尼卡|聖塔莫尼卡]]地區上空出現不明飛行物<ref name="Caughy">{{cite book|last1=Caughey|first1=John|last2=Caughey|first2=LaRee|title=Los Angeles: biography of a city|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YADTxxBmer8C&pg=PA364&dq=great+los+angeles+air+raid&hl=en&ei=VLDyS4K-OIXGlQeIw-GvDQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CCwQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=great%20los%20angeles%20air%20raid&f=false|year=1977|publisher=University of California Press|isbn=978-0-520-03410-5|access-date=2018-08-26|archive-date=2021-02-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210223192249/http://books.google.com/books?id=YADTxxBmer8C&pg=PA364&dq=great%20los%20angeles%20air%20raid&hl=en&ei=VLDyS4K-OIXGlQeIw-GvDQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CCwQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=great%20los%20angeles%20air%20raid&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Farley">{{cite book|last=Farley|first=John E.|title=Earthquake fears, predictions, and preparations in mid-America|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=N_pf4YBuu9wC&pg=PA14&dq=%22great+los+angeles+air+raid%22&hl=en&ei=s7nyS4CXM8SBlAf9-vjyDA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=5&ved=0CD4Q6AEwBA#v=onepage&q=%22great%20los%20angeles%20air%20raid%22&f=false|accessdate=17 May 2010|year=1998|publisher=Southern Illinois University Press|isbn=978-0-8093-2201-5|archive-date=2019-09-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190929062032/https://books.google.com/books?id=N_pf4YBuu9wC&pg=PA14&dq=%22great+los+angeles+air+raid%22&hl=en&ei=s7nyS4CXM8SBlAf9-vjyDA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=5&ved=0CD4Q6AEwBA#v=onepage&q=%22great%20los%20angeles%20air%20raid%22&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>。此時離[[珍珠港事件|珍珠港事件]]不到3個月，又先前（2月23日）日本剛進行{{link-en|埃爾伍德大轟炸|Bombardment of Ellwood}}，[[美軍|美軍]]因此認為可能是[[日本皇軍|日本皇軍]]的飛機。

當時的海軍部長{{link-en|法蘭克·那斯|Frank Knox}}在接下來的記者會上澄清，說這只不過是個「假警報」，報紙並刊登了一些報導及對這掩飾的猜測。一些現代的[[幽浮學家|幽浮學家]]認為這些目標其實是外星飛船。在1949年記錄事件時，美國海岸砲兵協會確定為氣象氣球出現於凌晨1點，射擊時想像出各種不同的目標猜測<ref name="AA">{{cite journal|last1=Murphy|first1=Col. John G.|title=Activities of The Ninth Army AAA - L.A. "Attacked"|journal=Antiaircraft Journal, The United States Coast Artillery Association|date=May–June 1949|volume=LXXXII|issue=3|page=5|url=http://sill-www.army.mil/ada-online/antiaircraft-journal/_docs/1949/5-6/May-June%201949%20Screen.pdf|accessdate=3 March 2016|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112013350/https://sill-www.army.mil/ada-online/antiaircraft-journal/_docs/1949/5-6/May-June%201949%20Screen.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。1983年的空軍歷史檔案庫（U.S. Office of Air Force History）將此事件歸咎於一顆遺失的氣象氣球及「對於戰爭的神經緊張」，並說後來的信號彈及防空砲火加劇了此事件。

==事件經過==
1942年2月24日，海軍情報發出警告，預計在未來十個小時內可能發生襲擊。當天晚上，國防工廠附近報告了大量的照明彈和閃爍的燈光。下午7點18分發出[[防空警報|防空警報]]，並於晚上10點23分解除警報。重新開始活動於25日清晨<ref name="OAFH">{{cite book |last1=Craven |first1=Wesley Frank |last2=Cate |first2= James Lea |title=The Army Air Forces in World War II: Defense of the Western Hemisphere |url= http://www.airforcehistory.hq.af.mil/Publications/titleindex.htm |accessdate=18 May 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090325191904/http://www.airforcehistory.hq.af.mil/Publications/fulltext/aaf_wwii-v1.pdf|archivedate=25 March 2009 |volume=1 |year=1983 |publisher=Office of Air Force History |location=Washington, D.C |isbn=978-0-912799-03-2 |pages=277–86 |chapter="West Coast Air Defenses", "The Battle of Los Angeles"}}</ref>。洛杉磯的空襲警報於凌晨2點25分響起<ref name=LATimes3>[http://www.latimes.com/local/lanow/la-me-battle-of-la-20170225-story.html# The Battle of L.A. turns 75: When a panicked city fought a Japanese invasion that never happened] {{Wayback|url=http://www.latimes.com/local/lanow/la-me-battle-of-la-20170225-story.html |date=20210226130751 }} LA Times</ref>。居民被命令全面[[燈火管制|燈火管制]]，千名{{link-en|空襲督導員|Air Raid Warden}}站上了他們的崗位。凌晨3點16分第37海岸砲兵旅開始發射重達5.8公斤的[[防空砲|防空砲]]，共發射了1400多發。第四攔截司令部的飛機已處於警戒狀態，雖然並未起飛。防空砲火並斷斷續續的發射直到凌晨4點14分。燈火管制的命令於早上7點21分解除<ref name="SI">{{cite web|last1=Boissoneault|first1=Lorraine|title=The Great Los Angeles Air Raid Terrified Citizens—Even Though No Bombs Were Dropped|url=https://www.smithsonianmag.com/history/great-los-angeles-air-raid-terrified-citizenseven-though-no-bombs-were-dropped-180967890/|website=smithsonianmag.com|publisher=[[Smithsonian_Institution|Smithsonian Institution]]|accessdate=5 May 2018|archive-date=2019-09-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190929062023/https://www.smithsonianmag.com/history/great-los-angeles-air-raid-terrified-citizenseven-though-no-bombs-were-dropped-180967890/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

數棟建築物與車輛被誤擊，大約5位平民死於防空砲火，其中有3位因無法承受長達數小時的炮火聲而死於[[心臟病|心臟病]]<ref>Niiya, Brian (1993). ''Japanese American History: An A-to-Z Reference from 1868 to the Present''. VNR AG, p. 112. {{ISBN|0816026807}}</ref>。此次事件上了美國西岸的報紙頭版，並引起了全國媒體的關注<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sfmuseum.net/hist9/aaf2.html |title=The Battle of Los Angeles – 1942 |publisher=Sfmuseum.net |date=25 February 1942 |accessdate=19 May 2010 |archive-date=2007-09-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070928095206/http://www.sfmuseum.net/hist9/aaf2.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

==媒體回應==
事件過後的數小時內，海軍部部長法蘭克那斯舉行了記者會，並說這只不過是因對戰爭的緊張所導致的{{link-en|假警報|False alarm}}。隔天陸軍的回應也引用了這段話<ref>''Los Angeles Times'', 27 February 1942</ref>，反映了陸軍上將[[喬治·卡特萊特·馬歇爾|喬治·卡特萊特·馬歇爾]]的想法：那些可能是商用飛機，用來投擲傳單，執行引發[[恐慌|恐慌]]的[[心理戰|心理戰]]罷了<ref name="milmuseum">{{cite web|url=http://www.militarymuseum.org/BattleofLA.html |title=California in World War II: The Battle of Los Angeles |publisher=Militarymuseum.org |date=25 February 1942 |accessdate=19 May 2010| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100527214255/http://www.militarymuseum.org/BattleofLA.html| archivedate= 27 May 2010 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref>。

當代的媒體認為這只是另一次的掩飾。一位{{link-en|長灘獨立報|Press-Telegram}}的編輯寫道「這整件事中有個神祕的沉默：某種程度的媒體審查似乎想停止關於這整件事情的討論。」（''There is a mysterious reticence about the whole affair and it appears that some form of censorship is trying to halt discussion on the matter.''）；有人認為在[[墨西哥|墨西哥]]北部有個秘密基地，也有人說日本具有[[航空潛艦|航空母艦功能的潛艦]]駐紮在外海；甚至說這整件事情被誇大了，要給沿海的國防工業一個藉口來搬到內陸<ref>''Los Angeles Times'', "Information, Please", 26 Feb. 1942, p. 1</ref>。

[[聖塔莫尼卡|聖塔莫尼卡]][[眾議員|眾議員]]{{link-en|利蘭·梅里特·福特|Leland M. Ford}}召開了國會調查（Congressional investigation），並說「......至目前為止的藉口都沒有讓這件事脫離『完全的謎團』......這可能是個演習，一場要嚇死兩百萬人的演習，也可能是假警報，只是要讓沿海的工業有藉口搬進內陸。」（''...none of the explanations so far offered removed the episode from the category of 'complete mystification' ... this was either a practice raid, or a raid to throw a scare into 2,000,000 people, or a mistaken identity raid, or a raid to lay a political foundation to take away Southern California's war industries.''）<ref>''Los Angeles Times'', "Knox Assailed on 'False Alarm': West Coast legislators Stirred by Conflicting Air-Raid Statements" 27 Feb. 1942, p. 1</ref>

== 幽浮學 ==
1942年2月26日在[[洛杉磯時報|洛杉磯時報]]發表的一張照片被一些幽浮研究者和陰謀理論家引用作為[[外星生命|外星生命]]探視證據的一部分，他們聲稱照片清晰地顯示了外星飛船的[[探照燈|探照燈]] ; 然而，照片在出版前進行大量修改，為當時用於提高黑白照片對比度的圖形藝術的常規做法<ref name=LATimes2>{{cite news|last=Harnisch|first=Larry|title=Another Good Story Ruined: Saucers Over L.A.! – Part 7|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/thedailymirror/2011/03/another-good-story-ruined-saucers-over-la-part-7.html|accessdate=3 April 2014|newspaper=Los Angeles Times|date=March 13, 2011|archive-date=2017-10-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171027210148/http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/thedailymirror/2011/03/another-good-story-ruined-saucers-over-la-part-7.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Ed Stockly|title=TV Skeptic: 'Fact or Faked: Paranormal Files' looks at the real 'Battle of L.A.'|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/showtracker/2011/03/tv-skeptic-fact-or-faked-paranormal-files-the-real-battle-of-la.html|newspaper=[[Los_Angeles_Times|Los Angeles Times]]|accessdate=2012-10-09|archive-date=2018-01-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180112234146/http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/showtracker/2011/03/tv-skeptic-fact-or-faked-paranormal-files-the-real-battle-of-la.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 紀念 ==
每年二月，位於[[洛杉磯港|洛杉磯港]]入口處的[[麥克阿瑟堡|麥克阿瑟堡]]博物館舉辦一場名為「1942年洛杉磯大空襲」的娛樂活動<ref name="MacArthur">{{cite web|url=http://www.ftmac.org/AirRaid2011.htm|title=Fort MacArthur Museum: The Great Los Angeles Air Raid of 1942|date=1994–2010|publisher=The Fort MacArthur Museum Association.|accessdate=19 May 2010|archive-date=2017-02-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202005309/http://www.ftmac.org/AirRaid2011.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

